    Binder
    This class is used to represent the binding between multiple nodes and an equivalent node
    This class is used when performing operations between MDD to bind multiple nodes, for instance x1 and x2 to a node x that would be the result of the combination of the two nodes.
    This is useful when you do not want to create many nodes that represent the same couple.

    MemoryObject
    MemoryObject is an interface that must be implemented if you want your object to be able to be reused.
    MemoryPool<E extends MemoryObject>
    The MemoryPool is the structure that contains all objects in the pool of memory. It is implemented using an array to stock the objects, and a stack to stock the indices of free objects, i.e their position in the array.
